      • createError

        public static SBMLError createError​(int id,
                                    int level,
                                    int version,
                                    boolean customMessage,
                                    SBase sbase)
        Creates a new SBMLError instance.
        Parameters:
        id - the error id
        level - the SBML level
        version - the SBML version
        customMessage - if true, the method will attempt to create a custom message passing the id of the given SBase
        sbase - an SBase which did provoke the SBMLError. If it's id is not define, no custom message will be returned.
        Returns:
        a new SBMLError instance.

      • getBundleString

        public static java.lang.String getBundleString​(java.util.ResourceBundle bundle,
                                               java.lang.String key)
        Gets the String corresponding to the given key in the bundle, returns null if the key is not found.

        This method catch MissingResourceException so that methods using it do not have to worry about it, they just have to deal with null values.

        Parameters:
        bundle - the ResourceBundle where to search
        key - the key to search in the bundle
        Returns:
        the String corresponding to the given key in the bundle, returns null if the key is not found.
